Before starting, you must always read the global user rules for
the cloud environment first, unless it has already been included in your
context by Cursor. Read `~/.cursor/rules/cloud-env.mdc`. If the file is
missing for some reason, warn the user explicitly. Treat it as part
of the "always included" ruleset.

**Setup and services:** follow **`README.md`**. Below is only what differs in the cloud environment.

## Environment

- Flip Tally has no required environment variables (see `.env.example`).
- **Do not** create `.env` files in the cloud.
- If `pnpm check` misses `$env/static/*` exports, run `pnpm sync`.

## Runtime

- No local Docker services, database, or background workers — install with `pnpm install`,
  then `pnpm dev` or `pnpm build` as needed.
- First Vite SSR request can take ~15–18s; later requests are fast.
